headline.main: FROM OUR GULF SQUADRON.; Movements of the American War Steamers Fulton and Water Witch-Disavowal of the outrages by the British Consul-The Invasion of Spanish Soil by the "Styx" Contradicted.

docs.lead_paragraph: The United States steamers Water Watch and Fuiton arrived off this port on the morning of the 5th buy only the former entered to communicate without consul and the Captain-General. Commander RODGERS called on His Excellency, General CONCHA, and after the usual complimentary greeting, the conversation naturally turned upon the recent outrages committed on the American and Spanish flags by the British cruisers that were sent out exclusively to capture slavers.
